===Noun===
{{ja-noun|k|hira=ひらがな|rom=hiragana}}
#A set of [[Japanese]] [[syllabary]] [[characters]] formed from cursive-style Chinese characters whose sounds approximate the Japanese sound being represented. Hiragana is mostly used for grammatical particles, verb-inflections, and Japanese words which are not written in [[kanji]] or which are too difficult for an educated person to read or write in kanji.

